column5: here is a trout caught in tough weather conditions..the bite was on for about 2 hours.. kept 1 and put 6 back.. all of them close to this size..we ate this one and he was just fine.. wish i could stay out longer but the wind was too strong boat would not hold
nice going, hope to get out there soon for a few of them
Very nice, were they deeper than usual?

most caught were in 75-85 feet but then again.. this guy we caught in 65 so who the hell knows..this is the first time we caught 6 trout in one day all in 2 hours of fishing..i think it was one of those days when the fish were  on the hunt..
Now that's a nice trout .I must try SIMCOE someday. WHAT lure did it hit on and time of day .?
